I have received 3 emails so far for new users and for the third one - Awesome Confluence Features and when you click on the link for Get Started it takes you to https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+101?utm_source=eval-email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=confluence-server-day-3  and on this page it says Confluence 101 Page Deleted.  A page with this title has been deleted.  Contact your space administrator if you would like it restored.  I just checked the previous email as well for Learn to master Confluence which takes you to https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Sharing+Content?utm_source=eval-email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=confluence-server-day-2  and it states on this page Page Not Found.  But does state that possibly the page was renamed to Collaboration which does indeed have information on Sharing Links in looking at the In other Spaces it lists older version of Sharing Content but I guess there isn't anything for the newest version. The information for Collaboration does appear to be the same as for Sharing so this one is somewhat OK and I can get the info needed.

Then went and checked the first one for your Welcome Kit and this one does resolve to the Getting Started with Confluence page at https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Getting+Started+with+Confluence?utm_source=eval-email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=confluence-server-day-1 - so at least one of them works, one mainly works but would be better if your link took you directly to the new Collaboration page and one of the links either had the content deleted by someone or possibly put somewhere else.  I am able to get to Confluence 101 via the Confluence Document home so that appears to be OK.

So either you need to clean up the emails you send to users to point to new locations for your documents or update your documentation.  Either way, this is not a good impression with users if this is their first experience with your tools.

