Often people want to print a file attachment that is being viewed in preview mode. Currently preview mode does not have a built-in option to Print - and if you try to use the Print functionality built into the browser, what shows up in the preview or gets printed is browser dependent - but definitely not what the user is trying to print.  Depending on the browser, it may contain most or all of the page and little or none of the attachment content that the user is trying to print.  

The current workaround is to download the file, open it on your desktop, and then print - but this is awkward and not what users are used to - especially with content like PDFs that browsers normally handle quite well as far as displaying and printing the file directly in the browser.

