Some pages are living documents that change with some frequency, and the changes impact a number of readers. The readers are tasked with staying up-to-date. Readers can best consume changes by viewing the History of the page to get a summary of what changes last time they visited. This change summary would be different for each user. What to do??

As a reader, I would like to press a "Got it!" button on the page I just read. Confluence would then associate the current page version with "me". Next time I visit the page I would like to press a "Show me recent changes" button (or some version of that in five letters :)), and Confluence would show the comparison between the latest version of the page and the version associated with "me".

